{{NCAATeamSeason |Mode = Basketball |Year = 2011â12 |Prev year = 2010â11 |Next year = 2012â13 |Team = Gonzaga Bulldogs |Image = GU Bulldog.svg |Image_size = |Conference = West Coast Conference |Division = |ShortConference = WCC |CoachRank = 18 |APRank = 19 |Record = 5â1 |ConfRecord = 0â0 |HeadCoach = [[Mark Few]] |HCYear = 13th |AsstCoach1 = [[Tommy Lloyd]] |AsstCoach2 = [[Ray Giacoletti]] |AsstCoach3 = [[Donny Daniels]] |StadiumArena = [[McCarthey Athletic Center]] |Champion = |BowlTourney = |BowlTourneyResult = }} {{2011â12 West Coast Conference men's basketball standings}} The '''2011â12 [[Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball]] team''' will represent [[Gonzaga University]] in the upcoming [[2011â12 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2011â12]] [[college basketball]] season. The Bulldogs (also informally referred to as the "Zags"), members of the [[West Coast Conference]], are led by head coach [[Mark Few]], in his 13th season at the school. The Zags play most of their home games at the [[McCarthey Athletic Center]] on the university campus in [[Spokane, Washington]], but take one home game a year to the [[Spokane Veterans Memorial Arena|Spokane Arena]], located in [[downtown Spokane]] about 2 miles (3 km) from the Gonzaga campus. The team also plays one game each season at [[KeyArena]] in [[Seattle]], a contest billed as the "Battle in Seattle".
==Preseason== In 2011â12, the Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball team were in their 32nd season as a member of the [[West Coast Conference]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wccsports.com/school-bio/west-school-bio.html|title=West Coast Conference History|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=November 13, 2011}}</ref> Since 2004, the team has played their home games at the [[McCarthey Athletic Center]], which has a capacity of 6,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gonzaga.edu/Academics/Libraries/Foley-Library/Departments/Special-Collections/exhibitions/GonzagaHistory1990.asp|title=Gonzaga History 1990-present|publisher=[[Gonzaga University]]|accessdate=November 13, 2011}}</ref>
